FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Everything you need to know about our tennis racket marketplace
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_1: How do I list my tennis racket for sale?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: To list your tennis racket, simply create an account, click on 'Sell a Racket', and follow the easy step-by-step process to upload photos and details about your racket.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: While we don't physically authenticate each racket, we have a robust user rating system and encourage buyers to thoroughly review listings. We also offer buyer protection for added peace of mind.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: We accept major credit cards, PayPal, and bank transfers. All transactions are securely processed through our platform to ensure safety for both buyers and sellers.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, we support international shipping. Sellers can specify their shipping options, and buyers can see estimated shipping costs before making a purchase.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: What if I'm not satisfied with my purchase?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: We have a 7-day return policy for most items. If you're not satisfied with your purchase, you can initiate a return through your account. Please note that return shipping costs may apply.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_1: How do I list my tennis racket for sale?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Listing your tennis racket is easy! Simply create an account, click on 'Sell a Racket', fill in the details about your racket including brand, model, condition, and price, then upload clear photos. Once submitted, your listing will be live for potential buyers to see.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: Are there fees for selling on this platform?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: We charge a small commission on successful sales to maintain the platform. The fee is 5% of the final sale price. There are no upfront costs for listing your racket.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: Sellers are responsible for shipping the racket to the buyer. We recommend using tracked shipping methods for security. The shipping cost can be included in the listing price or added separately. Buyers pay for shipping unless otherwise stated in the listing.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: What if I receive a racket that doesn't match the description?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: We have a buyer protection policy in place. If the racket you receive doesn't match the seller's description, you can initiate a return within 3 days of receipt. Our support team will review the case and assist in resolving the issue, including potential refunds if necessary.
